[The presence of significant fever and vomiting and a fairly short incubation period suggests that the pathogenic _E. coli_ in this outbreak is one of the other enteropaths of the organism. These include enterotoxigenic, enteropathogenic, enteroaggregative and enteroinvasive forms of _E. coli. - Mod.LL

